TASK: Fix Scramble Cat TUI freeze after async LLM response delivery.

CONTEXT:
The Scramble async refactor is almost working — the LLM call is non-blocking
(popen + O_NONBLOCK + poll from idle), the response arrives correctly, and it
gets displayed in the message view. But the ENTIRE TUI freezes immediately
after the response is shown. No clicks, no typing, no window moves work.

The callback was already moved from direct drawView-in-idle to posting a
cmScrambleReply (233) TV event via putEvent(), with delivery in handleEvent().
This STILL freezes.

Evidence from logs:
  [scramble] askAsync: starting non-blocking haiku call
  [scramble] async start: /Users/james/.local/bin/claude -p --model haiku...
  [scramble] async done: exit=0 result_len=70
  (then TUI is frozen)

KEY FILES:
- app/scramble_engine.h / app/scramble_engine.cpp — async startAsync/poll/cancelAsync
- app/scramble_view.h / app/scramble_view.cpp — TScrambleView (cat + bubble), TScrambleWindow (layout), TScrambleMessageView, TScrambleInputView
- app/test_pattern_app.cpp — wireScrambleInput() (~line 1622), deliverScrambleReply() (~line 1607), idle() (~line 2554), handleEvent cmScrambleReply (~line 1497)

KNOWN WORKING PATTERN:
The Wib&Wob Chat SDK provider uses the exact same approach — background thread
enqueues StreamChunks, poll() delivers them on main thread via timer — and it
works fine. Compare with app/llm/providers/claude_code_sdk_provider.cpp poll()
and app/wibwob_view.cpp timer handler.

THINGS TO INVESTIGATE:
1. Is putEvent() from inside idle() safe in Turbo Vision? (only one event slot)
2. Does TScrambleView's own 100ms timer handler conflict with the response delivery?
3. Is there a focus/select issue — the Scramble window trying to grab focus during redraw?
4. Does the TScrambleInputView lock up after the response (disabled, not re-enabled)?
5. Race between the idle-timer idle observations calling say() and the async response delivery

CONSTRAINTS:
- C++14, Turbo Vision TUI on arm64 macOS
- Build: cd build && make -j8 test_pattern
- Tests: cd build && ctest -R scramble --output-on-failure
- Do NOT break Wib&Wob Chat (which works fine)
- Do NOT remove idle observations or the timer — just fix the freeze

